President Obama spoke with Iraqi Prime Minister Haidar al-Abadi to discuss the political and security situation in Iraq and the United States' support in the fight against ISIL. The President praised the progress made by Iraqi forces against ISIL in Bayji and the ongoing campaign to isolate ISIL in Ramadi. The United States, in partnership with the Iraqi Government, will increase support for the Iraqi Security Forces. President Obama also expressed support for Prime Minister al-Abadi's efforts to combat corruption and implement governance reforms to promote Iraq's political stability and economic prosperity. Both leaders expressed their commitment to the U.S.-led Global Coalition to Counter ISIL and the strategic partnership between the United States and Iraq.